headline: The Smartest High-Yield Stocks to Buy With $2,000 Right Now
summary: The big news of late has been the quick decline suffered by the Nasdaq Composite (NASDAQINDEX: ^IXIC) and the S&P 500 index (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC), both of which fell into correction territory.  If you want to sidestep the worry, focus on collecting reliable dividends from companies like Realty Income (NYSE: O) and Toronto-Dominion Bank (NYSE: TD) instead.  Realty Income has trademarked the nickname "The Monthly Dividend Company," which speaks to the frequency of its dividend and to its commitment.
